        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add \"Hide critters\" toggle to render plain menu-bar meter bars ",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n  Fixes #1563 \r\n  Add a **\"Hide critters\"** toggle in Settings → Display that renders every\r\n  provider's menu-bar icon as plain capsule meter bars, dropping the\r\n  face/decoration drawn inside the top bar (the Codex eyes + hat, Claude crab,\r\n  Gemini/Antigravity sparkles, Factory gears, Warp eyes). Lets users who find\r\n  the critter faces look like a glitch/obstruction keep the usage bars without\r\n  switching to brand-icon-with-percent mode.\r\n\r\n  ## Implementation\r\n\r\n  - Added a persisted `menuBarHidesCritters` setting (default off)\r\n    - Threaded through `SettingsStoreState.swift`, `SettingsStore.swift`,\r\n  `SettingsStore+Defaults.swift`, and registered for menu observation in\r\n  `SettingsStore+MenuObservation.swift`\r\n  - Updated `Sources/CodexBar/IconRenderer.swift`\r\n    - Added a `hideCritters` parameter to `makeIcon` and `makeMorphIcon`\r\n    - Gated every decoration twist (`addFace` / `addNotches` / `addGeminiTwist`\r\n  / `addAntigravityTwist` / `addFactoryTwist` / `addWarpTwist`) behind computed\r\n  `twist*` booleans so the flag suppresses them while leaving the bar fills and\r\n  tracks intact\r\n    - Added `hideCritters` to both the icon cache key and the morph cache key so\r\n  toggling doesn't return a stale render\r\n  - Routed the flag through every live icon render path:\r\n  `StatusItemController+Animation.swift` (merged, per-provider, and morph),\r\n  `StatusItemController+Menu.swift`, and `MenuContent.swift`\r\n    - Added `hideCritters` to the render-skip signatures in `+Animation.swift`\r\n  and `+IconObservation.swift` so flipping the toggle repaints immediately\r\n  instead of being deduped\r\n  - Added the toggle row in `Sources/CodexBar/PreferencesDisplayPane.swift`,\r\n  placed below the merge-icons rows\r\n  - Added `hide_critters_title` / `hide_critters_subtitle` strings to `en` plus\r\n  the strict locales (`ar`, `fa`, `th`); remaining locales fall back to English\r\n  at runtime\r\n\r\n  ## Why\r\n\r\n  The critter faces are cut into the meter bar itself (`IconRenderer` `addFace`\r\n  et al.), so at menu-bar size the eye cutouts read as a stray mark obstructing\r\n  the bars — reported by users as looking like a rendering glitch. The only\r\n  existing escape was \"Menu bar shows percent,\" which replaces the bars with a\r\n  brand icon + text. This adds a way to keep the at-a-glance meter bars while\r\n  removing just the decoration, consistently across all providers.\r\n\r\n  ## Testing\r\n\r\n  - Rendered all 52 `IconStyle` cases with `hideCritters: true` and confirmed\r\n  each produces plain capsule bars (no faces, sparkles, dots, or eyes),\r\n  including the intro morph crossfade\r\n  - Ran `node Scripts/check-app-locales.mjs` — app locales OK (only pre-existing\r\n  non-strict warnings)\r\n  - Ran `swift build` — build complete\r\n\r\n  ## Screenshots\r\nBefore:\r\n\r\n\r\n<img width=\"550\" height=\"752\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-17 at 5 29 29 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c1d1c9b8-441a-4fca-8871-c18514fa16fc\" />\r\n<img width=\"103\" height=\"37\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-17 at 5 29 59 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5659ff29-7a26-461b-bedb-1070f74e39e1\" />\r\n\r\n\r\nAfter:\r\n\r\n\r\n<img width=\"550\" height=\"753\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-17 at 5 29 42 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/cb0e9f00-31af-4439-8f0c-52d3a0c12983\" />\r\n<img width=\"97\" height=\"34\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-17 at 5 30 03 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3811aa1f-094e-45b2-886b-6d67dc532c89\" />",
        "branch": "feature/hide-critters-toggle",
